==Fifth round==
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC fifth round}}

The two second-placed teams from the fourth round played against each other over two legs in November 2025 to determine which team advanced to the inter-confederation play-offs.<ref name="new format"/>

{{:2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC fifth round}}

==Inter-confederation play-offs==
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (inter-confederation play-offs)}}

The winner of the fifth round, [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]], joined [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] (from [[CONMEBOL]]), [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo]] (from [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]]), [[Jamaica national football team|Jamaica]] and [[Suriname national football team|Suriname]] (both from [[CONCACAF]]), and [[New Caledonia national football team|New Caledonia]] (from [[Oceania Football Confederation|OFC]]) in the inter-confederation play-offs.

The teams were ranked according to the November 2025 [[FIFA Men's World Ranking]], with the four lowest-ranked teams playing in two {{nowrap|single-elimination}} matches. The winners met the two highest-ranked teams in another set of {{nowrap|single-elimination}} matches, with the winners of these matches qualifying for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/play-off-tournament-draw-results|title=Path to 2026 laid out for Play-Off Tournament hopefuls|date=20 November 2025|access-date=20 November 2025|publisher=FIFA}}</ref>

